The paper proposes a novel end-to-end solution for predicting air quality using historical and real-time data. This involves the use of machine learning techniques such as Bidirectional LSTM Networks and adaptive attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also involves the use of data sources and information retrieval, which falls under cs.IR. Additionally, the paper deals with environmental issues and pollution control, which could fall under cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.CE (computers and society).
